00:46:59.500 --> 00:47:02.090
I'd love to know how.

00:47:02.090 --> 00:47:06.510
BURTON MALKIEL: Basically,
you can control the taxes

00:47:06.510 --> 00:47:12.250
by something that's called
tax loss harvesting.

00:47:12.250 --> 00:47:15.140
If you have a
portfolio-- let's say

00:47:15.140 --> 00:47:21.430
that you just have a
portfolio of US stocks,

00:47:21.430 --> 00:47:28.480
or even US technology
stocks, and it's an index.

00:47:28.480 --> 00:47:32.080
There are always going to be
a few of those stocks that

00:47:32.080 --> 00:47:33.200
have gone down.

00:47:33.200 --> 00:47:36.910
You've got Google,
that's gone up.

00:47:36.910 --> 00:47:43.820
You have Groupon,
that went down.

00:47:43.820 --> 00:47:48.070
So what you do in
tax loss harvesting

00:47:48.070 --> 00:47:54.110
is that you sell the loser
and put an equivalent one in.

00:47:54.110 --> 00:47:57.020
And we can do this
with index funds.

00:47:57.020 --> 00:48:01.700
We have a diversified
portfolio of US stocks,

00:48:01.700 --> 00:48:05.420
of international stocks,
of developed countries,

00:48:05.420 --> 00:48:09.360
of emerging market
stocks, of foreign bonds.

00:48:09.360 --> 00:48:12.660
In other words, we've got a
whole bunch of asset classes.

00:48:12.660 --> 00:48:17.820
So in a period such as this
past year, where the US stock

00:48:17.820 --> 00:48:21.970
market has gone way up, but
emerging markets have actually

00:48:21.970 --> 00:48:25.640
gone down-- emerging markets
have been weak this year--

00:48:25.640 --> 00:48:30.650
you sell one emerging market
index fund and buy another.

00:48:30.650 --> 00:48:36.720
So you keep the exposure,
but you recognize a loss,

00:48:36.720 --> 00:48:40.460
and that loss is
deductible from your taxes

00:48:40.460 --> 00:48:42.870
up to a certain
amount, or could be

00:48:42.870 --> 00:48:45.880
used to offset
other capital gains.

00:48:45.880 --> 00:48:50.960
So it's the harvesting
of the losses that

00:48:50.960 --> 00:48:55.750
is a way of
controlling your taxes.

00:48:55.750 --> 00:48:57.640
And again, up to
a certain amount,

00:48:57.640 --> 00:49:00.220
even if you had no
other capital gains,

00:49:00.220 --> 00:49:03.441
you could deduct this on
your 1040 for the year.

00:49:03.441 --> 00:49:04.940
ADAM NASH: This is
one of the things

00:49:04.940 --> 00:49:09.270
that humans can do-- if
