00:50:20.050 --> 00:50:22.230
BURTON MALKIEL: Well, you
are diversifying your risk

00:50:22.230 --> 00:50:24.720
using index funds.

00:50:24.720 --> 00:50:27.250
A lot of people will tell
me, because I believe

00:50:27.250 --> 00:50:30.120
in buying index funds
for emerging markets,

00:50:30.120 --> 00:50:32.790
and a lot of people make
the following argument.

00:50:32.790 --> 00:50:36.380
Look, emerging markets
are very inefficient.

00:50:36.380 --> 00:50:40.880
Information isn't, in fact,
as available for each stock

00:50:40.880 --> 00:50:45.450
as it is in, let's say,
the United States market.

00:50:45.450 --> 00:50:47.390
And that's absolutely correct.

00:50:47.390 --> 00:50:49.960
But when you look
at the data, you

00:50:49.960 --> 00:50:53.170
look at the data over
the last 10 years,

00:50:53.170 --> 00:50:56.420
and it's not 2/3
over that period who

00:50:56.420 --> 00:50:58.710
were worse than the index.

00:50:58.710 --> 00:51:04.990
It was basically over 90% of
active emerging market managers

00:51:04.990 --> 00:51:09.230
were worse than an
emerging market index,

00:51:09.230 --> 00:51:15.020
and it was in part almost
because of the inefficiency.

00:51:15.020 --> 00:51:18.430
The trading markets are
very inefficient in emerging

00:51:18.430 --> 00:51:18.960
markets.

00:51:18.960 --> 00:51:21.230
There are big bid-ask spreads.

00:51:21.230 --> 00:51:27.590
So if you trade, you're paying
a big gap, because you're always

00:51:27.590 --> 00:51:31.110
a buying at the ask price
and selling at the bid price.

00:51:31.110 --> 00:51:33.950
There are stamp taxes
in emerging markets,

00:51:33.950 --> 00:51:38.990
so that there's an extra
tax when you trade.

00:51:38.990 --> 00:51:42.580
When there are so-called
market impact costs,

00:51:42.580 --> 00:51:44.690
there's so little liquidity.

00:51:44.690 --> 00:51:47.710
So it's not like buying
500 shares of Google

00:51:47.710 --> 00:51:49.470
and you don't move the market.

00:51:49.470 --> 00:51:52.480
You move the price against you.

00:51:52.480 --> 00:51:59.690
And so even in markets
that seem less efficient,

00:51:59.690 --> 00:52:01.000
the markets are going to move.

00:52:01.000 --> 00:52:03.000
Different markets are
going to move differently.

00:52:03.000 --> 00:52:05.480
Emerging markets
are very unpopular.

00:52:05.480 --> 00:52:09.930
During that lost decade, when
the US market did nothing,

00:52:09.930 --> 00:52:12.600
emerging markets did 10% a year.

00:52:12.600 --> 00:52:18.666
During the last year, the
US market is up 15% plus,

00:52:18.666 --> 00:52:21.610
and emerging markets
were down 4% or 5%.

00:52:21.610 --> 00:52:25.620
So there is the opportunity
for tax loss harvesting,

00:52:25.620 --> 00:52:28.970
there is the opportunity
for diversification,

00:52:28.970 --> 00:52:33.080
and I don't see why you have
to go to individual stocks

00:52:33.080 --> 00:52:34.470
to get those opportunities.

00:52:34.470 --> 00:52:37.740
I think they're still
there with index funds,

00:52:37.740 --> 00:52:40.650
as long as you're in
different markets that

00:52:40.650 --> 00:52:42.875
react to different
economic realities.

